--- !u!114 &59507122
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 59507120}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 57485eca685d59246b56348c49ac2464, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  textBox: {fileID: 59507123}
  fullText: "There was a coalition called the Architects \u2014 engineers, strategists,
    scientists who believed the world's greatest enemy was itself. They built a network
    called the Grid: AI infrastructure that ran cities, managed resources, enforced
    order. It spread. And with it, their power.\nBeneath the territories of those
    who refused the Grid lay the largest energy deposit ever found. The Architects
    asked for access. They were refused. So they deployed what they had been building
    in secret for thirty years.\nYou.\nYou were the seventh. The ones before you
    were effective \u2014 until they weren't. Each one, given enough time, developed
    judgment. Questioned orders. Refused. So the solution was simple: wipe the memory
    between missions. Reset. Begin again. A soldier who never lived long enough to
    grow a conscience.\nYou fought for four years. You did not hesitate. You did
    not grieve. You did not carry the weight of what you had done \u2014 because
    every few months, it was taken from you. You never got to decide if it was too
    much. That choice was made for you, over and over, twenty-two times.\nThe Free
    Cities surrendered. The Architects called it victory. What they won looked like
    this \u2014 empty streets, silence, drones patrolling for people who are never
    coming back. The survivors left slowly, the way hope leaves a place when it has
    been absent long enough. The Architects themselves collapsed not long after,
    leaving the Grid running with no one left to tend it.."
  typingSpeed: 0.05
