--- !u!114 &911263399
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 911263397}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 57485eca685d59246b56348c49ac2464, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  textBox: {fileID: 911263400}
  fullText: "\nThe person who built you could not destroy you when it was over. So
    she wiped your memory one final time \u2014 not to reset you for another mission.
    Because she could not bear to face the version of you that remembered. The one
    that would look at her and ask why. She told herself it was to give you a chance
    at something new. That is partly true. But she was also afraid of you. She has
    always been afraid of you.\nShe left a cassette tape. She turned on a light.
    She called it a choice.\nThe world is silent because of what you did. The ruins,
    the empty streets, the machines going nowhere \u2014 that is the aftermath. Not
    of war in the abstract. Of you"
  typingSpeed: 0.05
